Reliance Industries (RIL) said it had signed agreements with Total SA of France for sale of its entire 76 per cent stake in Gulf Africa Petroleum Corporation (Gapco), for an undisclosed sum. &nbsp;

RIL had bought the 76 per cent stake in 2007, with management control. Gapco has significant presence in the downstream petroleum sector in Tanzania, Uganda, Rwanda and Kenya. RIL&rsquo;s foreign arm, Reliance Exploration and Production DMCC (REPD) had the 76 per cent; Fortune Oil Corporation, Mauritius, had the rest.

